fields.Title: BOARDWALK / WCH
fields.Description: Dead working class husband who has fallen through the blanks and cut himself open and it's generally a very gruesome and sad death.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Be very, very careful where you ste..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Be very, very careful where you step here.

fields.Title: You: ""No, just this one at the back of h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, just this one at the back of his head."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Well, at least you're not married...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, at least you're not married." The lieutenant points at the ring on the man's left hand, the flesh around it swollen and grey.

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "A dried chunk of blood covers the h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A dried chunk of blood covers the hair at the back of his head -- an open wound. It's sticky and cold to your touch.

fields.Title: You: ""It's hard to say.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's hard to say."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Seems like the head wound was fata..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Seems like the head wound was fatal. It's exactly the shape of the bench..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The next thing to do is call the s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The next thing to do is call the station from my Kineema and hand over the case. Then we can return to the murder investigation and be done with it."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes, yes," the lieutenant seems im..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, yes," the lieutenant seems impatient, "but what *actual* facts do you have that connect him with this woman you met at the bookstand?"

fields.Title: You: ""Looks like just another old drunka..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looks like just another old drunkard to me."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""A *sequence killer*?" The lieutena..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A *sequence killer*?" The lieutenant narrows his eyes in the wind. "There's nothing that connects those two bodies. This is a completely different case -- an accident."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Alright. We've already examined th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright. We've already examined the library card -- let's call the Jamrock Library from my Kineema, see if we can learn anything about this Billie MÃ©jean."

fields.Title: You: ""What do you think happened here?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you think happened here?"

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["boardwalk.corpse_studied_the_man"] == true  and  Variable["boardwalk.corpse_studied_clothes"] == true  and  IsKimHere()  and  Variable["boardwalk.corpse_studied_surroundings"] == true

fields.Title: Logic: "Or maybe it was just dark."
fields.Dialogue Text: Or maybe it was just dark.

fields.Title: You: ""Could it be related to the lynchin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Could it be related to the lynching?"
fields.Alternate1: "Could it be related to the lynching? Ruby?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""What about it? The deceased ate so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What about it? The deceased ate some kebab." He shrugs. "It's probably from a nearby place, maybe in the Pox..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Maybe, but we don't really have mu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe, but we don't really have much time or resources to spare. The guys at Processing will take care of the rest."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""A field autopsy isn't necessary if..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A field autopsy isn't necessary if the cause of death doesn't appear to be criminal -- and this looks like a simple accident to me."

fields.Title: Logic: "A cool leather jacket with a bolt o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A cool leather jacket with a bolt of blue? Oh no, this sounds terribly familiar...

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "This is an omen, a sign from above..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is an omen, a sign from above -- that you need to stop drinking.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "What if all of this is staged? He c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What if all of this is staged? He could have seen something that night in the yard...

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "They screech under your feet, omino..."
fields.Dialogue Text: They screech under your feet, ominously. It's hard to say whether the dead man's weight was what caused the boardwalk to break... It definitely looks fragile.
fields.Alternate1: The boards screech under the weight of the T-500 ceramic sabatons. It's a good thing they're so light, cause it's hard to determine whether it was the dead man's weight that caused the boardwalk to break... It definitely looks fragile.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "It's mid-market spirits. With a sli..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's mid-market spirits. With a slight touch of menthol. The man meant to enjoy himself, have a good time.

fields.Title: You: ""You're right, I don't see anything..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right, I don't see anything criminal here. Let's leave it at that."

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "The blackness of death. Stench. You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The blackness of death. Stench. You think you see white chewing gum too.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Oh yes," the lieutenant nods."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh yes," the lieutenant nods.

fields.Title: You: ""Who is this man?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Who is this man?"

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["boardwalk.corpse_studied_the_man"] == true  and  Variable["boardwalk.corpse_studied_clothes"] == true  and  IsKimHere()  and  Variable["boardwalk.corpse_studied_surroundings"] == true  and  Variable["boardwalk.corpse_who_is_this_man_done_alone"] == false

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Married to your drink, that's for s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Married to your drink, that's for sure.

fields.Title: You: ""What we're witnessing here is a de..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What we're witnessing here is a demise of a great party beast. That leather jacket, an empty vodka bottle..." (Kiss your fingers.)

fields.Title: You: ""You're right, connecting it with t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right, connecting it with the lynching is a stretch."

fields.Title: You: "Step back."
fields.Dialogue Text: Step back.

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "Careful. The wind blows hard, from..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Careful. The wind blows hard, from the east.

fields.Title: You: ""The library card! He was supposed..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The library card! He was supposed to return a book."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "The view from the lookout is beauti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The view from the lookout is beautiful...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The woman you met at the bookstand..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The woman you met at the bookstand?" He looks at the bundle of flesh and rags lying on the ground. "Why do you think it's her husband?"

fields.Title: You: ""The leather jacket." (Point at the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The leather jacket." (Point at the man's clothes.) "It matches her description perfectly."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Death by misadventure. He slipped..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Death by misadventure. He slipped and fell through the boardwalk. A truly unfortunate accident... If it wouldn't have been for that bench, he'd be alive."

fields.Title: You: ""Let's leave this case for the stat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's leave this case for the station, I don't want to spend time on it." (Don't take the case.)

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Alright. The station is going to w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright. The station is going to want details, however. Let's examine that library card you found on the man's body, see if it has any clues. Then we can call the station from my Kineema and hand over the case."

fields.Title: You: ""What if he *witnessed* something?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What if he *witnessed* something? All of this could be staged. We don't know the exact cause of death."

fields.Title: You: "Step on the floorboards."
fields.Dialogue Text: Step on the floorboards.

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "A man lies on the boardwalk, his li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A man lies on the boardwalk, his limbs bent and neck turned at an unnatural angle. Right next to him is an empty bottle of spirits. In his cramped hand: a chewing gum wrapper.
"Looks like he's been dead for a while. I'm surprised no one found him before you came along." He stands up and shivers as a gust of wind blows through his bomber jacket.
fields.Alternate1: "Looks like he's been dead for a while. I'm surprised no one found him before you came along." He stands up and shivers as a gust of wind blows through his jacket.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "In a ditch off a road below the 8/8..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In a ditch off a road below the 8/81, he thinks. A young father. Then he shakes his head, to make the memory stop.

fields.Title: Composure: "Calm now. Carefully. Just another d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Calm now. Carefully. Just another day, just another dead body. Breathe.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""But you're right, let's not run ah..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But you're right, let's not run ahead. For now all we know is that he's an unidentified middle-aged man found dead on the Martinaise boardwalk."

fields.Title: Perception (Smell): "The smell is... not as bad as a two..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The smell is... not as bad as a two-week-old corpse, but it's definitely heading there.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Alright. The station is going to w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright. The station is going to want details, however. We already examined the library card we found on the body -- good, that should be enough for the first lead."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Looks like he's been dead for a wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looks like he's been dead for a while. I'm surprised no one found him before you came along." He stands up and shivers as a gust of wind blows through his bomber jacket.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Lividity is faintly pronounced. Wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lividity is faintly pronounced. Whoever this is, he's been dead for two days, no longer." He stands up and shivers as a gust of wind blows through his bomber jacket. "We need to investigate."

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "The man has fallen through a crack..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The man has fallen through a crack in the boardwalk and hit his head against the metal bench. Coagulated blood covers his black hair. One of his feet is still dangling through the hole.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Looks like one of the locals -- he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looks like one of the locals -- he'd have to know this spot to come here. You don't *just* walk over here." He looks south, the way you came.

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "There's some dried blood on the met..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's some dried blood on the metal bench, right where the corpse's head rests. The floorboards are rotten and slippery wet around the hole. An empty bottle lies nearby. A chewing gum wrapper is clutched in his fist.

fields.Title: You: "Examine the man's head."
fields.Dialogue Text: Examine the man's head.

fields.Title: You: ""Yes, but... isn't that kind of slo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, but... isn't that kind of sloppy?"

fields.Title: Logic: "I'll have *one* drink before I get..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'll have *one* drink before I get home.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I don't see any other major wounds..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't see any other major wounds. Do you?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I'd prefer if you didn't collect t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'd prefer if you didn't collect them this time. It's not... proper."

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No, I don't see anything that poin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, I don't see anything that points in that direction. For now let's treat this case as a simple -- albeit sad -- accident, unrelated to the murder case."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""But let's try to not run ahead --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But let's try to not run ahead -- for now all we know is that he's an unidentified middle-aged man found dead on the Martinaise boardwalk."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""They'll seal this place off after..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "They'll seal this place off after the news reaches the Coalition officials. I doubt that they have enough resources to actually repair the boardwalk."

fields.Title: You: ""Right." (Conclude.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right." (Conclude.)

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Without any further evidence -- ye..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Without any further evidence -- yes."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Good call. The guys at Processing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good call. The guys at Processing can take care of the rest."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Alright. We should first examine t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright. We should first examine that library card you found. Then we can call the station from my Kineema, let them know we're taking the case."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Hold on..." The lieutenant leans o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hold on..." The lieutenant leans over the corpse and examines his face. Two glassy eyes stare back at him, void of any signs of life.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We should take another look at the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We should take another look at the library card you found on him," the lieutenant says, straightening his back.

fields.Title: You: "Search his pockets."
fields.Dialogue Text: Search his pockets.

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "First you need to talk with the lie..."
fields.Dialogue Text: First you need to talk with the lieutenant, then report back to the station. This is too complicated to handle on your own.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Well, he's definitely *someone's*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, he's definitely *someone's* husband." The lieutenant points at the golden ring on the man's left hand, the flesh around it swollen and pale.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""And he was married." The lieutenan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And he was married." The lieutenant points at the ring on the man's left hand, the flesh around it swollen and grey.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It does seem to be a pretty straig..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It does seem to be a pretty straightforward misadventure, although there's still the question of identifying the body..."

fields.Title: You: ""We should consider the possibility..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We should consider the possibility that we're dealing with a sequence killer here."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "This is where he came out of himsel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is where he came out of himself. Drop by drop when he was unconscious. It took three, maybe four minutes.

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "The entire boardwalk creaks in the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The entire boardwalk creaks in the wind as you take a step back.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""But I think that death arrived thr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But I think that death arrived through head trauma, not liver failure."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "True. It feels... disrespectful."
fields.Dialogue Text: True. It feels... disrespectful.

fields.Title: You: "Look in."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look in.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Confirmed. Nearly the whole pack is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Confirmed. Nearly the whole pack is there, solidified on his lower rear teeth.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Damn it... He's definitely *someon..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn it... He's definitely *someone's* husband." The lieutenant points at the golden ring on the man's left hand, the flesh around it swollen and pale.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I'd say we should just write down..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'd say we should just write down 'head trauma' and leave it at that. Let's keep this detour as short as possible -- the sooner we get back to finding Ruby the better."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""And while we're there we should al..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And while we're there we should also call the station, let them know that we're taking the case."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The bright blue lining?" He nods,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The bright blue lining?" He nods, then points at the ring on the man's left hand: "Well, he's definitely *someone's* husband."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Hold on..." The lieutenant squats..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hold on..." The lieutenant squats next to the corpse and examines his face. Two bulging eyes stare back at him, void of any signs of life.

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "He's wearing mud-caked boots, beige..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's wearing mud-caked boots, beige trousers and an old brown leather jacket with a bright blue lining. There are traces of kebab sauce on his chest.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "You have to be quite inebriated to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You have to be quite inebriated to fall that bad. Well over a litre of pure ethanol. Three bottles of wine or one and a half of spirits?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No need to rush.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No need to rush."

fields.Title: You: ""We know who this is. It's the work..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We know who this is. It's the working class woman's missing husband -- dead on the boardwalk."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I'd say we should just write down..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'd say we should just write down 'head trauma' in the autopsy report and leave it at that. It would save us at least two hours of unnecessary work."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Tare, all around us..." He looks a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Tare, all around us..." He looks at two other bottles forgotten near the coin-operated viewer.

fields.Title: Composure: "The leather jacket suits him well...."
fields.Dialogue Text: The leather jacket suits him well. It must be custom-made.

fields.Title: You: ""I still need some time to decide h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I still need some time to decide how I want to solve this case." (Return to this later.)

fields.Title: Logic: "A dead working class man with a bot..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A dead working class man with a bottle in his hand? Don't deceive yourself, you know who this is.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "This is an omen, a sign from above..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is an omen, a sign from above -- don't start drinking again.

fields.Title: Perception: "You see waves churning below... Som..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You see waves churning below... Something cracks beneath your feet.

fields.Title: You: ""What about alcohol poisoning and l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What about alcohol poisoning and liver failure?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Tare, all around us..." He looks a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Tare, all around us..." He looks at two other bottles near the coin-operated viewer, then at your yellow plastic bag.

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "You find some sunflower seeds and a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You find some sunflower seeds and a rain-soaked library card, folded into two. His jacket feels sodden and heavy under your hand.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Height: 170-175 cm, curly hair, sto..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Height: 170-175 cm, curly hair, stout build. Age: approximately 50-60 years.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""From where I stand I can see two o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "From where I stand I can see two options. We either take the case and follow the leads to identify the body on our own -- or we report back to the station and leave this for our colleagues to handle."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes, but... I just wanted to make..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, but... I just wanted to make it clear it's not a sequence killer, okay?"

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "'Rubowski' spearmint chewing gum. G..."
fields.Dialogue Text: 'Rubowski' spearmint chewing gum. Green leaves on the cover. The man's mouth is half-agape from the terror of the fall...

fields.Title: You: ""Bottles, all around him." (Point a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Bottles, all around him." (Point at the tare.) "She said he was drinking somewhere in Martinaise."

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "Only some sunflower seeds remain in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Only some sunflower seeds remain in his soaked pockets. You already took the library card.

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "His expression is dull like the sea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: His expression is dull like the sea behind him, drops of water shining on his moustache. His eyes, empty and wide, look frightening in their frozen gaze.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Or what if you are...?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Or what if you are...?

fields.Title: Half Light: "Yes, but what if there's a killer o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, but what if there's a killer on the loose? Two suspicious deaths in such a short time frame!

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's possible, but let's take it s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's possible, but let's take it step-by-step. We still haven't identified the man."

fields.Title: You: ""I'm just saying that we should be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm just saying that we should be open to all possibilities."

fields.Title: Logic: "This is what killed him."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is what killed him.

fields.Title: Logic: "A bad fall. It might have been dark..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A bad fall. It might have been dark outside? This place is a mine field in the dark.

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "A man lies on the boardwalk, his li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A man lies on the boardwalk, his limbs bent and neck turned at an unnatural angle. Right next to him is an empty bottle of spirits. In his cramped hand: a chewing gum wrapper.

fields.Title: You: "Study the man's clothes."
fields.Dialogue Text: Study the man's clothes.

fields.Title: You: ""I think labelling him as an alcoho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think labelling him as an alcoholic is a bit premature. We don't know anything yet."

fields.Title: You: ""Someone should be held responsible..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Someone should be held responsible for this broken boardwalk. It's dangerous."

fields.Title: Working Class Corpse: "A 0.75 litre 'Touloula' vodka with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A 0.75 litre 'Touloula' vodka with its cap missing. There's hardly anything left inside.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant shudders from the co..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant shudders from the cold. "I've seen it before: almost the same scenario. Even the chewing gum. It's always the same..."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Just one drink. I have my cool jack..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just one drink. I have my cool jacket on. I took the book to the library. I've earned it.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Because it's the most working class..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Because it's the most working class death you've ever seen.

fields.Title: You: ""He looks like me. I could have end..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He looks like me. I could have ended up just like him -- dead on some empty boardwalk with a bottle next to my corpse."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Good, we should take a look at tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good, we should take a look at that library card after this is done."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Half of his body has slipped betwee..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Half of his body has slipped between the cracked boardwalk, starting with the right leg. The fall has left him broken, contorted like a sad puppet.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I can't see a book..." The lieuten..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can't see a book..." The lieutenant pats his pockets. "So he took the book to the library, then came back and thought -- I'll have one."

fields.Title: You: "Study the man himself."
fields.Dialogue Text: Study the man himself.

fields.Title: You: ""What should we do with him?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What should we do with him?"

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["boardwalk.corpse_studied_the_man"] == true  and  Variable["boardwalk.corpse_studied_clothes"] == true  and  IsKimHere()  and   Variable["boardwalk.corpse_talked_with_kim_about_what_to_do"] == false  and  Variable["boardwalk.corpse_studied_surroundings"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.identify_corpse_boardwalk"] == false  and   Variable["TASK.report_corpse_wo_taking_main_task"] == false

fields.Title: You: "What should I do with the body?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What should I do with the body?

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["boardwalk.corpse_studied_the_man"] == true  and  Variable["boardwalk.corpse_studied_clothes"] == true  and  IsKimHere() == false  and  Variable["boardwalk.corpse_studied_surroundings"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.identify_corpse_boardwalk"] == false  and   Variable["TASK.report_corpse_wo_taking_main_task"] == false

fields.Title: You: ""Do you think he was drunk?" (Point..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you think he was drunk?" (Point at the bottle.)

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "He could have easily disappeared in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He could have easily disappeared into the sea through that hole. And you would have never found him.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "He was *just* about to head home. T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He was *just* about to head home. The first step back home proved to be his last.

fields.Title: You: "Examine the chewing gum wrapper."
fields.Dialogue Text: Examine the chewing gum wrapper.

fields.Title: Logic: "That's what the chewing gum seems t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's what the chewing gum seems to point to as well.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Not that sealing it off would keep..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not that sealing it off would keep anyone away. All it does is keep the city council's hands clean." He smiles sourly.

fields.Title: You: ""Someone could have pushed him from..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Someone could have pushed him from behind with an intention to kill."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Some symptoms of acute alcohol poi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Some symptoms of acute alcohol poisoning could have definitely played a role here: severe confusion, respiratory depression, unpredictable behaviour..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""He ate the whole pack, right? It's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He ate the whole pack, right? It's to cover the smell of alcohol before going home. The worst thing is..."

fields.Title: Logic: "Agreed. If this somehow converges l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Agreed. If this somehow converges later, why not. But keep it simple for now.

fields.Title: Logic: "Sometimes a kebab is just a kebab."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sometimes a kebab is just a kebab.

fields.Title: You: ""This is the most working class way..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is the most working class way to go -- completely alienated and forgotten."

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "When damp these boards are really s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: When damp these boards are really slippery, even a sober man could loose their balance here.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""But that's just a lazy assumption...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But that's just a lazy assumption. What do you think?"

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "At least this man knew how to party..."
fields.Dialogue Text: At least this man knew how to party! Imagine the same scene without the bottle -- now that would be just sad.

fields.Title: You: "Study the surroundings."
fields.Dialogue Text: Study the surroundings.

fields.Title: You: ""Hold on -- what about field autops..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hold on -- what about field autopsy?"

fields.Title: You: "Examine the bottle."
fields.Dialogue Text: Examine the bottle.

fields.Title: Authority: "Another dead body. This is your job..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Another dead body. This is your job. Steel yourself.

fields.Title: You: ""We found him. We should finish thi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We found him. We should finish this." (Take the case.)

fields.Title: You: "Back off."
fields.Dialogue Text: Back off.

fields.Title: Logic: "To hide the stench of alcohol no do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: To hide the stench of alcohol no doubt.

fields.Title: You: "Examine his face."
fields.Dialogue Text: Examine his face.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We do know that he was married." T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We do know that he was married." The lieutenant points at the ring on the man's left hand, the flesh around it swollen and grey.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The wedding ring." The lieutenant..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The wedding ring." The lieutenant points at the ring on the man's left hand, the flesh around it swollen and grey.

fields.Title: You: ""What about the kebab?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What about the kebab?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "He was confused when he died. Confu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He was confused when he died. Confused and alone, most likely. Overcome with the awful surprise of it all.
